                                 <div class=sectline>Sequence in context: <a href="/A180005" title="Numbers n with the property that the relation 1-d!/((d-i)!d^i)&gt;1/2 holds for integers d&gt;2 between i-1 and n+i-1.">A180005</a> <a href="/A116958" title="Numbers k such that 2*k + 5 and 2*k + 7 are twin primes.">A116958</a> <a href="/A242477" title="a(n) = floor(3*n^2/4).">A242477</a> * <a href="/A171370" title="Sequence generated from Lim:_{n..inf.} M^n, M = an infinite lower triangular matrix with (1,3,3,3,...) in every column, shif...">A171370</a> <a href="/A061776" title="Start with a single triangle; at n-th generation add a triangle at each vertex, allowing triangles to overlap; sequence give...">A061776</a> <a href="/A356020" title="Positions of records in A356018, i.e., integers whose number of evil divisors sets a new record.">A356020</a></div>
                             
                                 <div class=sectline>Adjacent sequences:  <a href="/A006153" title="E.g.f.: 1/(1-x*exp(x)).">A006153</a> <a href="/A006154" title="Number of labeled ordered partitions of an n-set into odd parts.">A006154</a> <a href="/A006155" title="Expansion of e.g.f.: 1/(2-x-exp(x)).">A006155</a> * <a href="/A006157" title="a(n+1) = (n-1)*a(n) + n*n!.">A006157</a> <a href="/A006158" title="a(n) = a(a(n-3)) + a(n-a(n-3)).">A006158</a> <a href="/A006159" title="a(n)=a(a(n-4))+a(n-a(n-4)).">A006159</a></div>
                             
                         </div>
